<CaseStudyLayout
  title="Complex Survey Prevalence"
  description="Case study: design-weighted prevalence estimation across multiple exposure groups with survey-adjusted variance and subgroup summaries."
  field="Epidemiology · Survey"
  status="Methods Showcase"
  problem="Multiple exposure products are increasingly used in combination, but comparative health-impact data across exclusive and poly-use groups remains fragmented, motivating a nationally representative analysis."
  approach="Build a complex survey design object from multi-cycle data with sampling weights, strata, and PSU clusters, then fit survey-weighted logistic and linear regression across nine mutually exclusive exposure groups, with stratified subgroup and sensitivity analyses."
  outcome="Produces design-weighted, survey-adjusted effect estimates and confidence intervals for each exposure group, plus subgroup summaries by sex and age band and sensitivity checks under alternative exposure definitions."
  figures={figures}
  code={code}
